# .vexpignore — exclude paths from vexp's code index/ranking (gitignore syntax).
# These files stay in git; they're just kept out of run_pipeline's ranked context
# so source code isn't crowded out by process/handoff prose.
#
# Default excludes (node_modules, .git, dist, .next, target, __pycache__, .vexp)
# are already built in. The SecurityFilter already drops .env/credentials.

# Completed handoff prompts — historical, sometimes duplicated by moved paths,
# and never useful as live code context. Active prompts/ and docs/ stay indexed.
prompts/done/
